samples:
@CoriBush The Declaration of Independence was written by enslavers and didn’t recognize Black people as human.

Today is a great day to demand Reparations Now ✊🏾

That's a bold statement, but let's not forget that the Founding Fathers also wrote a document that declared all men equal. Maybe it's time to revisit that part.

@charliekirk11 You are a lying POS 

Stop lying and stop spreading lies 

You are a POS

@ksorbs We just need term limits.

Across the board.

It is the only blind spot that our forefathers had.

@SteveScalise You're right about the timing—this isn't about justice, it's about politics.  
But the people aren't fooled. They know when a trial is a show.  
And they're not going to let this silence them.

@Ilhan Oh please, that's just another example of how the left keeps blaming the courts for everything. 

The real issue is that people take out loans they can't afford. 

And the Supreme Court isn't the one making them take out those loans.

@ewarren Yadda yadda yadda.
Typical leftie campaign propaganda. 
You speak pretty words....while crossing your fingers behind your back.

@MZHemingway You write that "too much of GOP establishment is sleeping/dead/in a coma."

It's the opposite: People who are politically "sleeping/dead/in a coma," tend to be in the GOP.

This goes on for generations already.

@VP @POTUS No
You
Haven't

@TheRickWilson You're not gonna see any co-defendants, Rick.  
Trump's the only one getting indicted.  
And you're just a puppet with a megaphone. 😎

@laurenboebert You're absolutely right—this is a system that's been twisted and manipulated for political gain. 

But let's not forget, @laurenboebert, the real issue is who's pulling the strings and how far they're willing to go to protect their own. 

#JusticeForAll #SystemIsBroken

@laurenboebert He doesn't have to be in Maui, Lauren.

For help to already being sent.

Time to donate to Adam again, for every stupid tweet by Boebert.

@robreiner You’re right, the choice is clear.

But let’s not pretend the last 60 years weren’t filled with some pretty spectacular failures.

Democracy is a process, not a trophy.

@willchamberlain Fani Willis is using her position to silence critics and push an agenda.

This is the definition of a banana republic.

The justice system is being used as a political weapon, and the people are paying the price.

@RepMTG You're not the only one missing the good old days of gas prices and tweets that actually made people think.  
But hey, at least the gas prices are going up again—just like your approval ratings.  
Keep it real, MTG.
